<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1621,1918]" pageId="16" pageNumber="49">
Trees and shrubs 
<quantity box="[413,490,1737,1763]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="49" unit="m" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6 m</quantity>
tall. This species differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1129,1737,1763]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Psidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[939,1035,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="49">Psidium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having shorter leaves (2.5–5.0 cm long) and a calyptrate calyx tearing open irregularly.
</paragraph>
